// Given an n×n binary grid (1=open, 0=blocked),
// start at (0,0), find all paths to (n-1, n-1)
// moving only DOWN or RIGHT.
// Output the count of valid paths.
// Constraints: n <= 10
// Example:
// grid = [[1,0,0],
//         [1,1,0],
//         [0,1,1]]
// Answer: 1  (path: down, down, right, right... blocked elsewhere)

